MUCH algae- slight wind- big storm 2 days ago with large tree damage- leaves + dirt on houses and windows- and debris in lake.  Clumps of blue-green algae as well as routinely seen flecks of algae.  Active boat with tubing in testing area.
a bit windy but no white caps.  Few boats in area but no skiers or tubing.  sunny/partly cloudy nice cool day with low humidity.
no wind- thick stinky algae with blooms at shore and 150-200 feet out but less in middle of bay- heavy rain yesterday- mostly sunny with high clouds- hot and humid (90 degrees).
light south winds and sunny- no boat traffic- thick black algae yesterday but mostly blown out today- high water level for unknown reason.
8-9 mph winds from northwest- green algae flecks throughout- gorgeous sunny clear day- small amount boat traffic.
sunny with moderate wind- very cool=45 degrees- no boat traffic- much algae even in middle of lake.  Performed by kayak.
very sunny with light winds- 72 degrees- small amount boat traffic-algae blooms at shore and lots of algae throughout.  Performed by kayak.
very cloudy- rain predicted- no wind....lake like glass- no boats- algae clumps and sediment throughout.  Buoys out with no gps so unsure of accurate location but fairly close.  Performed by kayak.
lake like glass- no wind- no boat traffic- water very clear--can see to bottom at shoreline.

no wind- lots of algae throughout lake and putrid at shoreline.
